      "author": "arias007",
      "description": "Cancip 0.1.206 packages an offline neural TTS runtime directly with the Obsidian plugin.\n\nHighlights:\n- Built-in Piper Plus TTS provider is now the default.\n- Auto TTS resolves to the bundled Piper Plus package instead of falling through to system/Web/network fallbacks.\n- Bundles multilingual model, ONNX Runtime Web WASM, Piper Plus Rust WASM, and Chinese pinyin dictionaries under `tts/piper-plus`.\n- No APK handoff, no Android share-sheet reading, no temporary public network TTS, and no mechanical eSpeak/meSpeak fallback.\n- Includes accumulated Cancip UX, review gate, memory routing, skill, attachment, and automation improvements since 0.1.178.\n\nInstall:\n- For normal Obsidian manual install, download `cancip-0.1.206-plugin-with-piper-plus-tts.zip` and extract the contained `cancip` folder to `.obsidian/plugins/cancip`.\n- First Android TTS run can be slow while the ONNX/WASM runtime initializes.\n\nVerification performed locally:\n- `npm run check`\n- `npm run build`\n- `node --check outputs/cancip/main.js`\n- Installed plugin manifest verified as 0.1.206\n- Release zip verified to contain 8 Piper Plus TTS resource files, 115,821,663 bytes total.\r\n",
      "downloadCount": 2,
